lead_paragraph: The cameras in the Senate are government controlled by the Senate staff, and photographs are not allowed — limiting what viewers can see as lawmakers consider the case against President Trump. To get a more complete picture of the proceedings, here are two alternatives.

abstract: For many Americans, how they feel about issues raised during President Donald Trump's impeachment has much to do with where they get their news.
snippet: For many Americans, how they feel about issues raised during President Donald Trump's impeachment has much to do with where they get their news.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — For many Americans, how they feel about issues raised during President Donald Trump's impeachment has much to do with where they get their news.
headline_main: Study Links Impeachment Beliefs to Regular News Diets
headline_print_headline: Study Links Impeachment Beliefs to Regular News Diets

abstract: Even the goal of defeating President Trump isn’t enough for some voters to commit to backing the eventual Democratic nominee, expressing a clear aversion to a candidate who is too liberal or centrist for their tastes.
snippet: Even the goal of defeating President Trump isn’t enough for some voters to commit to backing the eventual Democratic nominee, expressing a clear aversion to a candidate who is too liberal or centrist for their tastes.
lead_paragraph: FORT DODGE, Iowa — Democrats have always represented a cacophonous array of individuals and interests, but the so-called big tent is now stretching over a constituency so unwieldy that it’s easy to understand why voters remain torn this close to Iowa, where no clear front-runner has emerged.

abstract: The president began his social media assault just after 6 a.m.
snippet: The president began his social media assault just after 6 a.m.
lead_paragraph: President Trump complained Friday that his lawyers would begin his defense on Saturday, a day the president said in the world of television was “called Death Valley,” as he unleashed dozens of tweets and retweets attacking the Senate trial.
headline_main: Trump complains about a Saturday start to his defense, a ‘Death Valley’ on TV.

abstract: This is their last opportunity to appeal to a handful of moderate Republican senators in hopes of seeking additional witnesses and documents.
snippet: This is their last opportunity to appeal to a handful of moderate Republican senators in hopes of seeking additional witnesses and documents.
lead_paragraph: The House managers prosecuting the case against President Trump will wrap up their arguments on Friday with a focus on the second article of impeachment: the accusation that the president obstructed Congress by blocking witnesses and documents in an attempt to cover up his misconduct.

abstract: The European Union’s top diplomat said Friday that more time is required to unravel a dispute between countries involved in the Iran nuclear agreement, as the Europeans struggle to keep alive a deal hampered by U.S. sanctions.
snippet: The European Union’s top diplomat said Friday that more time is required to unravel a dispute between countries involved in the Iran nuclear agreement, as the Europeans struggle to keep alive a deal hampered by U.S. sanctions.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Union’s top diplomat said Friday that more time is required to unravel a dispute between countries involved in the Iran nuclear agreement, as the Europeans struggle to keep alive a deal hampered by U.S. sanctions.
headline_main: EU Seeks More Time in Effort to Resolve Iran Nuclear Dispute
headline_print_headline: EU Seeks More Time in Effort to Resolve Iran Nuclear Dispute

abstract: For wealthy Davos men and women, as well as people from less rarefied air, targeted investing is one way to force change on carbon-emitting companies.
snippet: For wealthy Davos men and women, as well as people from less rarefied air, targeted investing is one way to force change on carbon-emitting companies.
lead_paragraph: Climate change has been a key theme this week at the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, with big ideas being bandied about, and big-picture proposals being announced.

abstract: Proposed changes to further limit American shipments to Huawei have been delayed amid arguments they could backfire.
snippet: Proposed changes to further limit American shipments to Huawei have been delayed amid arguments they could backfire.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration has temporarily shelved a proposed rule change that would further restrict American sales to Huawei, the Chinese telecom giant, after some officials in the Defense Department and other agencies argued that the measure, which was intended to protect national security, could actually undermine it, according to people familiar with the matter.
